.TH "bitmap_print_to_pagebuf" 9 "bitmap_print_to_pagebuf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bitmap_print_to_pagebuf \- convert bitmap to list or hex format ASCII string
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" bitmap_print_to_pagebuf
.BI "(bool list "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ","
.BI "const unsigned long *maskp "  ","
.BI "int nmaskbits "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "list" 12
indicates whether the bitmap must be list
.IP "buf" 12
page aligned buffer into which string is placed
.IP "maskp" 12
pointer to bitmap to convert
.IP "nmaskbits" 12
size of bitmap, in bits
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Output format is a comma-separated list of decimal numbers and
ranges if list is specified or hex digits grouped into comma-separated
sets of 8 digits/set. Returns the number of characters written to buf.

It is assumed that \fIbuf\fP is a pointer into a PAGE_SIZE, page-aligned
area and that sufficient storage remains at \fIbuf\fP to accommodate the
\fBbitmap_print_to_pagebuf\fP output. Returns the number of characters
actually printed to \fIbuf\fP, excluding terminating '\0'.
